{
  "stem": "11998.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Actually, they occupied Lodz before they occupied Hoshiv, because they went around Silesia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They didn't want to destroy any of the land that  they eventually annexed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was my first time that I went to Lodz, and I met my family there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I went, too, many times as a child.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Lodz was quite far away from Hoshiv, but Czestochowa was a couple hours by train.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we used to go to bar mitzvahs, and weddings, and family affairs, and just to visit my grandparents.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my grandparents only spoke Yiddish, so I had to learn Yiddish and write letters to them in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, living in Hoshiv, we had three languages.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "German, which the-- a lot of people in the town spoke German.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Most of the kids that I associated with were non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We lived-- Hoshiv had a very small Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It had one synagogue and one [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I would say that there were maybe 500 families, maybe between 300 and 500 families in Hoshiv.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So it was-- Jewish families.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So there was a small community.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The town was most likely-- I don't know exactly, but I would say somewhere between 50,000 and 100,000 people.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a very industrial and dirty town, a lot of coal mines and smelters.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we went to school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I went to school.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We went to a Jewish school which was formed by the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it was-- we were taught in Polish, and the rabbis come and-- to teach us-- I don't remember if it was twice or three times a week that he came and taught us Bible.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then, of course, he had to go through cheder, which was separate.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it was an equal but separate school.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
